$interpreted: Elio: Miss Fatima, will this amount of vines be alright?
Fatima: Hmm, this amount shouldn't affect the habitat of this area. If we add in the share of those three brats, should be enough.
Elio: Understood. I'll go pass this information to them.
Fatima: Oh, right. Umm...
Fatima: I apologize for my previous comments. Didn't mean to be so rude...
Elio: It's okay. I'm already used to it.
Fatima: You can blame Charle for that. Can't believe that man; how could he not mention something as important as him having a child!
Elio: Your meetings with him are mostly to discuss serious business. That's probably why he didn't feel the need to talk about me.

Fatima: Hmph, I bet it's because he wants to maintain fairness as the headmaster. He doesn't want other people to think that he has favoritism towards you.
That's why he doesn't actively talk about you.
Fatima: Could it be that in the Academy, you two also refer to each other as headmaster and student?
Elio: Miss Fatima, how did you know that!?
Fatima: Sighs... This way of thinking is just so... him...
Elio: ... To be fair, I also don't want the things I achieved through my own efforts be misinterpreted by other students as a result of me relying on father...
Annie: We will never think like that!
Annie: Elio's efforts were never overlooked! We've all seen it with our own eyes. We know that you work much harder than so many other people!
Cara: That's right! You don't have to pay attention to the naysayers! Those people just don't understand who you really are!
Betty: The one we look up to and admire is Elio the person, not headmaster Ceres's son!
Elio: You guys...

Fatima: Hahaha...
That's some pretty nice comments coming from you three brats!
？？？: He ran this way!
Panther Traitor: Fatima! Why are you here?
Fatima: I remember that you guys are...
Panther Traitor: Damnit! Kill them before they can talk!
Annie: HELP!
Elio: Sis Annie, Sis Betty, Sis Carla!

Panther Traitor: Another step and all three of them will die!
We retreat first!
Fatima: You're one of the warriors who was supposed to oversee the isolated Panthers. What happened exactly?

Panther Warrior: Ugh... Those isolated Panthers...
They bribed the warriors who were overseeing them...
Panther Warrior: Then they... they launched an attack against us...

Fatima: So someone had the gall to do this to fellow panthers!
Who is the mastermind behind this!?
Panther Warrior: J, Jerus...
Elio: Miss Fatima, what exactly is going on?
Fatima: Apologies for getting you guys involved in Panthers' inner conflict. However, we don't have time to report back to the Panther tribe now!
Fatima: I need to rescue those three brats as soon as possible. Can you lend me a hand?
Elio: All three of them are my friends. Of course I will help!
Fatima: Very well. We'll go into details as we chase them down. This way!
